White House Budget Director
Mick Mulvaney said Mr.
Trump is unhappy with

03:24.633 --> 03:26.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
portrayals that Democrats
won the budget fight.

03:26.666 --> 03:29.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY, White House
Budget Director: The president
is frustrated with the fact

03:29.766 --> 03:32.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he negotiated in good
faith with the Democrats and
they went out to try and spike

03:32.866 --> 03:34.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the football and
make him look bad.

03:34.933 --> 03:37.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It doesn't surprise me at
all that his frustrations
were manifested in that way.

03:37.466 --> 03:41.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have got a lot to do
-- we have got a lot to
between now and September.

03:41.366 --> 03:46.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't anticipate a shutdown in
September, but, if negotiations
-- if the Democrats aren't

03:46.300 --> 03:49.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
