to dig with to bury her,

19:41.966 --> 19:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
so we just put grass on
the body and left it there.

19:44.733 --> 19:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Marco
Nuer is 16 years old and
also goes to school here.

19:51.766 --> 19:53.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two months ago, he made it
to this village with what
remained of his family.

19:53.733 --> 19:58.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCO NUER, South Sudan (through
translator): When we fled
the fighting, I saw at least

19:58.066 --> 19:59.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
20 people killed.

19:59.666 --> 20:02.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Along the road later,
people died of hunger.

20:02.366 --> 20:07.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: His brother,
sister and father were among
those who died of starvation.

20:09.366 --> 20:13.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The trauma of their
loss haunts him.

20:13.200 --> 20:18.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Both Rebecca and Marco have
found safety in this village
controlled by rebel gunmen.

20:20.166 --> 20:23.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rebecca's family have been
given this small hut to
shelter in by local people.

20:23.166 --> 20:28.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her mom, Tipasa, tries to sell
tea to make extra money for
food, but it's never enough,

20:30.366 --> 20:32.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
so she forages in the marshes.

20:32.966 --> 20:36.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
These are the roots of
the water lily flowers.

20:36.233 --> 20:40.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is all people in this part
of South Sudan have to eat.

20:40.433 --> 20:41.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's muddy.

20:41.966 --> 20:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It has very little nutritional
value and is deeply unpleasant.

20:45.300 --> 20:49.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is what they ate when
they were hiding in the bush,
too, and how countless numbers

20:49.900 --> 20:54.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of people in South Sudan are
trying to survive, on the run
from government troops targeting

20:55.800 --> 20:58.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
them because of their tribe.

20:58.433 --> 21:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A split between president Salva
Kiir and his vice president,
Riek Machar, in 2013 tore

21:04.566 --> 21:08.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
apart the country,
sparking a civil war.

21:08.000 --> 21:11.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Both sides have been
accused of war crimes.

21:11.133 --> 21:16.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most recently, government
soldiers have been
attacking communities of
tribes seen as supportive

21:18.100 --> 21:21.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Machar's rebel fighters,
killing civilians and forcing
large groups of people to flee.

21:23.433 --> 21:25.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They run into these
massive swamps.

21:25.666 --> 21:30.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is a good hiding place from
soldiers hunting them, but
there is nothing to eat here, so

21:32.100 --> 21:35.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
famine has come to both
Marco and Rebecca's homes.

21:35.766 --> 21:39.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is a cruel
manmade disaster.

21:39.400 --> 21:44.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is food in South Sudan,
but many have had to leave
it behind when they flee.

21:47.100 --> 21:52.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Food is being dropped by aid
agencies to the most desperate.

21:55.833 --> 22:00.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Those with the strength
come out of hiding to
get lifesaving supplies.

22:00.400 --> 22:03.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is Leer, the famine
area where Marco is from.

22:03.900 --> 22:07.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People here used to grow their
own vegetables and farm cattle.

22:07.266 --> 22:12.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When they ran for their lives
into the bush, they left behind
any way of feeding themselves.

22:15.100 --> 22:19.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The International Committee
of the Red Cross is giving
them tools and seeds.

22:19.100 --> 22:24.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If they plant maize now, they
can harvest it by August,
if they live that long.

22:26.066 --> 22:30.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In many ways, this area is
symbolic of the link between
war and hunger in South Sudan.

22:32.200 --> 22:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An area where aid agencies
are giving out food to local
people, they say this once was

22:36.233 --> 22:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a vibrant marketplace, until
government troops came in
and burned it to the ground.

22:42.833 --> 22:46.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And now the only thing
left of that market is
just ash on the ground.

22:46.133 --> 22:51.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The numbers of those in
need here are staggering;
100,000 people are right
now starving to death

22:52.766 --> 22:54.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
across the country.

22:54.600 --> 22:56.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Millions more are on the brink.

22:56.633 --> 23:00.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEEPMALA MAHLA, Mercy Corps:
Before I came here, I thought,
I know the drill, I have

23:00.533 --> 23:02.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
been there.

23:02.533 --> 23:06.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have never seen anything more
complicated, more saddening
as compared to South Sudan;

23:07.700 --> 23:09.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
4.8 million people do
not have enough food.

23:09.866 --> 23:12.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It really shocks me.

23:12.466 --> 23:16.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Deepmala
Mahla runs the U.S.-based
charity Mercy Corps'
operation in South Sudan.

23:17.266 --> 23:19.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
She is not optimistic
for the future.

23:19.800 --> 23:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEEPMALA MAHLA: I have
to say the gap between
being brink of starvation
and actually starving,

23:23.433 --> 23:25.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
there isn't a whole
lot of time left.

23:25.566 --> 23:29.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It happens -- the deterioration
happens pretty fast.

23:29.066 --> 23:34.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: South Sudan
is the most dangerous
place in the world for
aid workers, yet people

23:35.233 --> 23:37.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
here desperately
needs their help.

23:37.700 --> 23:42.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Over 80 have been killed since
the war started, a fifth of
those in this year so far alone.

23:44.533 --> 23:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Aid agencies often
struggle to reach people
starving in the wilderness.

23:48.233 --> 23:53.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Flying for hundreds of miles
over this vast country, you
rarely see even a dirt road.

23:55.300 --> 23:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's in these remote areas
where people are dying,
far from the world's view.

24:01.366 --> 24:05.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People in urban areas like the
capital, Juba, can get help.

24:05.266 --> 24:08.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
International Medical
Corps runs this hospital.

24:08.366 --> 24:13.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the intensive care ward
for children, Dr. Sadia
Azam shows us how she
diagnoses malnutrition.

24:14.300 --> 24:16.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, she is in danger?

24:16.233 --> 24:18.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

24:18.133 --> 24:20.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SADIA AZAM, International
Medical Corps: Yes,
she is in danger.

24:20.133 --> 24:22.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
She is really
acute malnourished.

24:22.466 --> 24:24.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JANE FERGUSON: What's
causing that for her?

24:24.733 --> 24:25.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

24:25.866 --> 24:27.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SADIA AZAM: The
children are like this.

24:27.600 --> 24:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Their bodies are very fragile.

24:29.700 --> 24:31.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They are very weak.

24:31.433 --> 24:36.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: And weak bodies
can't fight off deadly diseases.

24:36.066 --> 24:39.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One-and-a-half-year-old
Nyagoah also has pneumonia.

24:39.633 --> 24:44.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
This hospital exists
largely because of U.S.
government funding.

24:44.500 --> 24:48.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
American money is responsible
for much of the aid relief
in South Sudan, whether it's

24:48.600 --> 24:53.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
food drops from planes
or the seeds and tools
distributed in famine areas.

24:55.666 --> 24:58.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Cuts to foreign aid proposed
by the Trump administration
could mean less money makes

24:58.400 --> 24:59.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it here.

24:59.400 --> 25:01.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And charities are nervous.

25:01.633 --> 25:05.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Jason Straziuso is the
regional spokesperson
for the International
Committee of the Red

25:05.566 --> 25:07.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Cross.

25:07.600 --> 25:09.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JASON STRAZIUSO, International
Committee of the Red Cross: The
United States is the largest

25:09.133 --> 25:13.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
single supporter of the ICRC, a
substantial part of our budget.

25:13.800 --> 25:18.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we view this
American generosity and
goodwill as vital to our
operations, as vital to our

25:21.633 --> 25:24.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
humanitarian assistance
around the world.

25:24.766 --> 25:29.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JANE FERGUSON: Rebecca
escaped the horrors of
widespread killings,
only to face starvation

25:30.500 --> 25:32.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the wilderness.

25:32.566 --> 25:36.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Famine will continue to stalk
families like hers in this
country for as long as people

25:36.400 --> 25:40.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
cannot peacefully farm their
cattle and grow food at home.

25:40.766 --> 25:44.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the war that drives
hunger here is far from over.

25:44.400 --> 25:49.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Jane Ferguson in
Unity State, South Sudan.

25:51.366 --> 25:55.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In her final
report tomorrow, Jane brings us
the stories of women in South

25:56.833 --> 26:00.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sudan who have survived rape
used as a weapon of war.

26:10.600 --> 26:12.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Stay with us.

26:12.666 --> 26:16.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
home visits that cut back on
the risks and cost of asthma;

26:18.566 --> 26:22.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and from our "NewsHour"
Bookshelf, a new perspective
on a polarizing president.

26:24.066 --> 26:28.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But first: Can a dramatic
depiction of suicide go too far?

26:28.033 --> 26:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A new series on Netflix about
a teenage girl's tragic death
has some school districts and

26:35.100 --> 26:39.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mental health experts worried
that the show has gone beyond
just entertainment, and could

26:39.900 --> 26:41.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pose a threat to young students.

26:41.766 --> 26:43.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham
explores the controversy.

26:43.566 --> 26:46.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's part of our weekly
series Making the Grade.

26:46.200 --> 26:49.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And a warning: The story
contains graphic content.

26:49.466 --> 26:53.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATHERINE LANGFORD,
Actress: Some of you cared.

26:53.766 --> 26:55.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
None of you cared enough.

26:55.966 --> 26:58.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Neither did I.

26:58.100 --> 27:03.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: "13 Reasons
Why" tells the fictional story
of Hannah Baker, a 17-year-old

27:04.133 --> 27:06.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
high school student
who takes her own life.

27:06.733 --> 27:11.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hannah leaves behind 13 cassette
tapes, where she narrates
the events leading up to her

27:12.200 --> 27:13.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
suicide.

27:13.433 --> 27:14.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KATHERINE LANGFORD:
Hey, it's Hannah.

27:14.100 --> 27:16.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Hannah Baker.

27:16.133 --> 27:19.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Each tape
centers around one person, and,
in it, Hannah tries to explain

27:21.233 --> 27:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
why that person was or wasn't
to blame for her death.

27:24.533 --> 27:28.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATHERINE LANGFORD: Don't
adjust your -- whatever
device you're hearing this on.

27:28.333 --> 27:30.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's me, live and in stereo.

27:30.433 --> 27:34.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Get a snack, settle in, because
I'm about to tell you the story
of my life, more specifically

27:39.333 --> 27:41.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
why my life ended.

27:41.000 --> 27:45.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And if you're listening
to this tape, you're
one of the reasons why.

27:47.400 --> 27:50.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The
show, which was released
in its entirety a month
ago, brutally depicts

27:50.833 --> 27:53.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some very tough topics: hazing,
cyber-bullying, and rape.

27:53.933 --> 27:58.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Hannah's own rape by one of her
classmates is unsparingly shown.

28:00.966 --> 28:05.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The series is based on a
2007 young adult novel by Jay
Asher, and it was produced by

28:05.833 --> 28:07.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
singer Selena Gomez.

28:07.833 --> 28:11.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Since its release, school boards
around the country have sent
warning letters to parents,

28:11.533 --> 28:16.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alerting them to the show,
offering ways to talk about its
content with their kids, but

28:17.966 --> 28:20.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
also suggesting that some kids
probably shouldn't watch it.

28:20.633 --> 28:25.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Among the concerns cited is
the very explicit way Hannah's
suicide is shown in the final

28:26.100 --> 28:27.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
episode.

28:27.600 --> 28:31.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATHERINE LANGFORD: Pardon me,
but you really hurt my feelings.

28:31.666 --> 28:35.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Some
psychologists say it
glorifies suicide.

28:35.733 --> 28:38.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Others worry it could
lead to copycat behavior.

28:38.700 --> 28:43.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The National Association
of School Psychologists
advised teenagers who
suffer from suicidal

28:43.433 --> 28:48.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
thoughts not to watch
at all, saying it "may
lead impressionable
viewers to romanticize

28:49.566 --> 28:51.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the choices made
by the characters."

28:51.600 --> 28:56.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Both groups found fault with
the notion of Hannah sending
these taped messages from beyond

28:56.600 --> 29:01.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the grave, and criticized the
depiction of a school counselor
on the show who, they argue,

29:03.000 --> 29:05.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fails to follow up on
Hannah's obvious distress.

29:05.400 --> 29:09.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Following the outcry, Netflix
says it will add a warning
at the beginning the series,

29:09.466 --> 29:12.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in addition to the
warnings in front of the
most graphic episodes.

29:12.900 --> 29:17.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And from the beginning, the
show's creators say they
consulted mental health experts,

29:17.266 --> 29:20.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and tried hard not
to glamorize suicide.

29:20.600 --> 29:22.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Brian Yorkey is one of
the show's creators.

29:22.633 --> 29:26.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRIAN YORKEY, Co-Creator, "13
Reasons Why": We did want it
to be painful to watch, because

29:26.466 --> 29:31.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we wanted it to be very clear
that there is nothing in any
way worthwhile about suicide.

29:35.400 --> 29:39.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: We asked
the "NewsHour"'s own Student
Reporting Labs to ask some high

29:39.233 --> 29:42.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
schoolers for their
take on the series.

29:42.000 --> 29:44.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Some applauded the show.

29:44.033 --> 29:47.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JULIA, Student: I thought the
series would help students that
were grappling with suicide,

29:47.566 --> 29:52.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just because the show promoted
awareness for students who deal
with suicide and depression,

29:55.066 --> 29:57.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and they wanted it to
start conversations.

29:57.733 --> 30:02.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it became so popular and
so many people were talking
about it, that I felt like it

30:02.066 --> 30:04.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
did.

30:04.200 --> 30:08.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
STUDENT: I really think
that it's important for
adults to know how much
social media impacts

30:08.000 --> 30:10.066 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
us now.

30:10.066 --> 30:14.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's a different time,
and social media is one
of the biggest reasons
why suicide happens

30:17.133 --> 30:19.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nowadays.

30:19.233 --> 30:20.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Others were
concerned about how the show
dealt with suicide and mental

30:20.933 --> 30:22.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
health.

30:22.866 --> 30:25.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ZOIE, Student: I feel like
there is a lot of younger
