38:38.600 --> 38:39.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CHRISTINA CONOLLY:
Thank you for having me.

38:39.766 --> 38:44.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SONIA SARAIYA:
Thank you, William.

38:46.166 --> 38:51.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Roughly
25 million people in the
U.S. have active asthma.

38:53.166 --> 38:57.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For most, it can be controlled
with the right medications
and by avoiding environmental

38:57.800 --> 39:00.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
triggers.

39:00.366 --> 39:03.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And yet nearly half
of all adults and 40
percent of children have
uncontrolled asthma, which

39:05.000 --> 39:07.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
can lead to expensive
medical interventions.

39:07.733 --> 39:12.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Total annual costs
for the disease are
estimated at $60 billion.

39:12.633 --> 39:17.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today is World Asthma Day, which
makes it a good moment for this
report by special correspondent

39:19.566 --> 39:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Cat Wise about a California
program that's drawing attention
for its way of keeping kids

39:24.633 --> 39:27.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
healthy.

39:27.100 --> 39:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Three-year-old Jesus
Cresto (ph) has been to the
emergency room twice in the

39:35.933 --> 39:38.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
past 12 months for
asthma attacks.

39:38.433 --> 39:41.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
His mom, Angelica (ph),
says she isn't getting
much sleep these days.

39:41.466 --> 39:42.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANGELICA CRESTO, Mother: I
will just be checking on him.

39:42.533 --> 39:44.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is he OK?

39:44.000 --> 39:46.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's really hard, because
they change your life.

39:46.033 --> 39:50.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I just want to take
care of my kids better.

39:50.266 --> 39:55.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CAT WISE: The Cresto
family lives in East
Oakland, a predominately
low-income community

39:57.233 --> 39:59.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Alameda County ,which has
some of the highest rates
of asthma in California.

39:59.433 --> 40:04.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Children with uncontrolled
asthma, especially those from
low-income families, who often

40:04.033 --> 40:08.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have government-funded health
care insurance, account
for a disproportionate
number of costly

40:08.800 --> 40:10.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
E.R. visits and hospital stays.

40:10.833 --> 40:15.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, keeping Jesus and the more
than one million other kids with
asthma in California healthy

40:16.466 --> 40:18.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is a big priority.

40:18.933 --> 40:22.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Alameda County has
been leading an effort
to do just that, focusing
on the place where

40:23.300 --> 40:27.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
kids spend the most
time, their home.

40:29.566 --> 40:32.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On a recent morning, a team
of cleaners specializing
in asthma trigger
remediation, arrive at the

40:32.833 --> 40:34.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Cresto home.

40:34.833 --> 40:38.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They cleaned up pest droppings
behind the fridge, removed
mold spots on a bedroom window,

40:38.500 --> 40:41.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and put a dust mite
cover on a mattress.

40:41.366 --> 40:45.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The cleaning visit was
arranged by Sandra Rodriguez, a
community outreach worker from

40:45.866 --> 40:48.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the county's Healthy
Homes Department.

40:48.533 --> 40:52.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She is part of a unique
collaboration between housing
and public health agencies.

40:52.666 --> 40:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SANDRA RODRIGUEZ, Alameda
County Healthy Homes Department:
Where does Jesus spend a lot of

40:55.133 --> 40:56.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the time?

40:56.666 --> 40:59.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANGELICA CRESTO: He usually
likes to be on the floor.

40:59.066 --> 41:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, how I clean the
house, I use Clorox a lot.

41:03.433 --> 41:04.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SANDRA RODRIGUEZ: OK.

41:04.966 --> 41:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANGELICA CRESTO: Because I think
I want to keep the floors clean.

41:07.733 --> 41:12.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SANDRA RODRIGUEZ: Using harsh
chemicals like Clorox can really
exacerbate a child's asthma.

41:14.766 --> 41:19.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so we recommend that you try
natural products, just soap and
water, soap and water, and one

41:20.500 --> 41:22.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the additional
is baking soda.

41:22.400 --> 41:24.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANGELICA CRESTO: OK.

41:24.533 --> 41:28.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: The program, which
began in 2001 and was among
the first of its kind in the

41:28.166 --> 41:32.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country, is open to all
children in the county who have
been diagnosed with asthma.

41:32.500 --> 41:36.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Allergen-reducing products
like HEPA filter vacuums are
offered to families who can't

41:36.666 --> 41:40.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
afford them, and the
program will even pay
for minor home repairs.

41:40.100 --> 41:42.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BRENDA RUEDA-YAMASHITA,
Alameda County Public
Health Department: We
saw these very high

41:42.166 --> 41:46.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rates in our county, and we
didn't want to have residents
who were dealing with issues

41:46.133 --> 41:48.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like that.

41:48.200 --> 41:51.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Brenda Rueda-Yamashita
manages the Public Health
Department's side of the program

41:51.166 --> 41:53.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
called Asthma Start.

41:53.300 --> 41:57.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She says the up-front costs,
which average about $2,500
per family, depending on the

41:57.700 --> 42:01.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
needs, are worth spending to
prevent the back-end costs.

42:01.100 --> 42:05.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRENDA RUEDA-YAMASHITA: It's
around $23,000 for a child to
have an asthma hospitalization,

42:05.466 --> 42:10.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and around $3,500 for an E.R.
visit, so that's the highest
impact, mom losing money, dad

42:12.400 --> 42:14.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
losing money, because they have
to stay home with a child or
take the child to the E.R.,

42:14.833 --> 42:17.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and their employer
doesn't pay for sick time.

42:17.333 --> 42:22.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a cost to cities
and/or counties for their fire,
because fire departments show

42:22.233 --> 42:24.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
up to 911 calls.

42:24.266 --> 42:28.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: The other key priority
for the program is educating
families about the importance

42:28.200 --> 42:31.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of taking prescribed
asthma medications.

42:31.233 --> 42:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's where medical social
worker Amy Sholinbeck comes in.

42:41.900 --> 42:46.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On this day, she is back for
a second visit with 2-year-old
Romani Webb (ph) and his mom,

42:46.733 --> 42:48.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Artency (ph).

42:48.733 --> 42:52.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Romani has had several hospital
stays for asthma attacks,
but after an initial two-hour

42:52.266 --> 42:56.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
visit a month ago, the
family has been on top
of his medications.

42:56.166 --> 42:59.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY SHOLINBECK, Medical Social
worker: Have you noticed that
he's been having less symptoms

42:59.600 --> 43:01.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
since you have been doing this?

43:01.166 --> 43:02.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARTENCY WEBB, Mother: At
the nighttime, definitely.

43:02.100 --> 43:03.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He sleeps a lot better too.

43:03.333 --> 43:04.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
AMY SHOLINBECK: Oh, I'm
so happy to hear that.

43:04.766 --> 43:06.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's all about his health.

43:06.400 --> 43:09.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We want to keep you out
of the hospital, baby.

43:09.466 --> 43:14.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sometimes, the family ends up
confusing the inhalers, or it
wasn't explained to them in

43:15.066 --> 43:17.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
enough detail.

43:17.100 --> 43:20.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we're in a calm environment
in their home, and we take a
lot of time to make sure they

43:22.066 --> 43:24.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
understand what the
medications do in the body.

43:24.366 --> 43:29.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we have special stickers
we put on the medicines, and
we just make sure they really

43:30.066 --> 43:31.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
get it.

43:31.533 --> 43:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: I just want to give
you an update on our numbers.

43:33.033 --> 43:37.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CAT WISE: The program has served
about 250 families each year.

43:37.300 --> 43:41.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's been funded through
a combination of sources,
including grants, taxes, tobacco

43:41.400 --> 43:44.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
settlement money, and a local
Medicaid managed-care program.

43:44.833 --> 43:49.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
A data review by that
organization in 2012
found health care costs
for pediatric patients

43:51.800 --> 43:56.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ages 0 to 5 were cut in half
during the 12 months after
they went through the program.

43:58.000 --> 44:02.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those results and the program's
long track record are generating
new interest in Alameda

44:02.500 --> 44:04.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
County's preventative approach.

44:04.533 --> 44:07.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDA NEUHAUSER, University of
California, Berkeley: I have
studied a lot of programs,

44:07.400 --> 44:12.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but when I got introduced
to this program, what I
saw was a very seasoned,
careful intervention

44:14.066 --> 44:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that draws on the best
practices that we get
from research to date.

44:20.533 --> 44:23.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: U.C., Berkeley,
Professor Linda Neuhauser is
leading an in-depth study of

44:23.566 --> 44:25.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the program.

44:25.600 --> 44:28.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her research is ongoing, but
she believes policy-makers
around the country should pay

44:28.800 --> 44:30.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
attention.

44:30.866 --> 44:34.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDA NEUHAUSER: It's hard
to estimate the cost savings,
but I think, in Alameda County

44:36.800 --> 44:40.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alone, we might be able to
save as much as $16 million a
year just on hospitalizations

44:43.066 --> 44:44.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of children.

44:44.533 --> 44:47.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is an amazing saving
of health care costs.

44:47.300 --> 44:52.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Eight-year-old Mihlen
Michael (ph) is one of those
children who is happy to be

44:52.166 --> 44:54.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out of the hospital.

44:54.066 --> 44:58.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A year ago, she was in
intensive care after an
especially bad asthma attack.

44:58.233 --> 45:02.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her mom, Nebiyat Hagos (ph),
says some big changes have
happened since the asthma teams

45:02.633 --> 45:04.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
visited their home.

45:04.166 --> 45:06.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NEBIYAT HAGOS, Mother: Now
she's doing a lot better.

45:06.100 --> 45:08.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
She hasn't been to
the E.R. in a year.

45:08.700 --> 45:10.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They made a great difference.

45:10.733 --> 45:15.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We were living close to a
freeway, and they mentioned
to me how that affects asthma.

45:16.633 --> 45:19.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, we moved away
from the freeway now,
and that also helped.

45:19.200 --> 45:23.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CAT WISE: Hagos is now working
for the program, and using the
training she received to help

45:23.533 --> 45:25.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
other families with asthma.

45:25.600 --> 45:29.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The home-based asthma program
recently got a temporary boost
in funding from a national

45:29.800 --> 45:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
nonprofit and the Alameda
County Board of Supervisors.

45:33.200 --> 45:38.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That money is being used in
part to help an additional
250 families this year.

45:39.800 --> 45:43.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Cat Wise in Alameda
County, California.

45:45.866 --> 45:50.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally tonight,
a new look at one of the
most controversial American

45:56.866 --> 46:00.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
presidents in modern history and
a man of many contradictions.

46:00.733 --> 46:04.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Jeffrey Brown has this
latest addition to the
"NewsHour" Bookshelf.

46:04.466 --> 46:09.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Few presidents,
we read early is a new
biography of Richard Nixon, came

46:09.433 --> 46:14.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so far, so fast, so alone,
and, we can add, few fell
so far, so fast, so alone.

46:16.433 --> 46:21.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
More than that, as "Richard
Nixon: The Life" makes clear,
so much of his political legacy

46:21.233 --> 46:23.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
continues to permeate today.

46:23.033 --> 46:25.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Author John A.
Farrell joins me now.

46:25.800 --> 46:27.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And welcome to you.

46:27.366 --> 46:28.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN A. FARRELL,
Author, "Richard Nixon:
The Life": Thank you.

46:28.866 --> 46:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Let me start
there for some broad context.

46:30.933 --> 46:34.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In what fundamental way is
Richard Nixon still with us
in our political culture?

46:34.433 --> 46:39.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN A. FARRELL: Nixon
practiced what I call the
politics of grievance.

46:41.333 --> 46:44.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He came from a very unfortunate
background, almost a Dickensian
childhood, with a mean

46:46.866 --> 46:50.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
father, a very frosty
mother, poverty and
sickness in the household.

46:52.800 --> 46:56.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he had that ability
to identify in his
audiences, in the electorate
their own resentments,

46:57.000 --> 46:59.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and to tap them.

46:59.033 --> 47:03.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he didn't realize until the
end, the famous speech where
he talks about hate destroying

47:04.500 --> 47:07.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
yourself, how
dangerous that was.

47:07.100 --> 47:12.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, by then, this sort
of politics of deliberate
polarization that he
pioneered had taken root.

47:13.900 --> 47:16.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It was so
interesting to me to see the
younger Nixon, even in his first

47:16.866 --> 47:21.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
time running, where you get
the mix of the kind of sincere
ambition to serve, but already

47:23.900 --> 47:28.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a lot of the tricks, the
bad side of Nixon, it was
there from the beginning.

47:28.600 --> 47:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN A. FARRELL: Yes, it's one
of the things I found was that
Nixon, throughout his life,

47:32.100 --> 47:36.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was always using yellow pads
and making lists, and then
crossing out as he went.

47:36.533 --> 47:41.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, he comes home from war
in 1946, and like lots of the
younger veterans, having seen

47:43.100 --> 47:45.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the sacrifices that
were made, they wanted
to improve their world.

47:45.133 --> 47:48.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They wanted to make sure those
sacrifices weren't in vain.

47:48.066 --> 47:51.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's where that idealism
that you talked about came from.

47:51.266 --> 47:55.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, young congressional
candidate, there was also
this dark side already.

47:55.900 --> 47:59.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And he was running
against a fellow named
Jerry Voorhis in 1946.

47:59.766 --> 48:04.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in one of these
yellow lists, as I went
down ticking them off,
you know, get volunteers,

48:06.733 --> 48:10.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
put ads in newspapers,
and there at the bottom
was the instruction,
put spies in Voorhis

48:10.100 --> 48:11.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
camp.

48:11.100 --> 48:12.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Put spies...

48:12.333 --> 48:14.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JOHN A. FARRELL: Put
spies in his camp.

48:14.133 --> 48:16.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, right from the
beginning, he had that
inclination towards intrigue.

48:16.700 --> 48:21.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: One bit
of news that you make in
this book is confirming
his role in sabotaging

48:23.466 --> 48:27.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the Paris peace talks,
right, the attempt to
end the Vietnam War.

48:27.100 --> 48:29.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN A. FARRELL: Yes.

48:29.200 --> 48:31.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He didn't want
his Democratic opponents to
get credit for ending the war.

48:31.366 --> 48:33.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN A. FARRELL: That's right.

48:33.366 --> 48:35.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lyndon Johnson desperately
wanted to end the war
before he left office.

48:35.366 --> 48:39.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And in October 1968,
he announced a bombing
halt to bring the North
Vietnamese and the

48:40.600 --> 48:42.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
South Vietnamese to the table.

48:42.666 --> 48:46.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Nixon got wind of it, and
dispatched a woman named Anna
Chennault, who was one of

48:46.433 --> 48:51.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his aides in his campaign, to
approach the South Vietnamese
and say, drag your heels,

48:53.100 --> 48:55.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
scuttle the talks, and
you will get a better
deal when I'm elected.

48:55.066 --> 48:57.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And he denied it all his life.

48:57.166 --> 49:01.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He denied it in one of the taped
conversations that you can hear
at the Lyndon Johnson Library.

49:02.166 --> 49:04.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He denied it directly.

49:04.200 --> 49:08.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I was able to find the
little, tiny jigsaw piece that,
again, one of those yellow legal

49:09.966 --> 49:12.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
pad notes, this time from his
chief of staff, Bob Haldeman.

49:12.466 --> 49:15.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: You end
up calling this his
most reprehensible act.

49:15.733 --> 49:17.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN A. FARRELL: I think it was.

49:17.766 --> 49:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because of the number of lives
that were at stake, for a
presidential candidate to do

49:23.800 --> 49:27.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this, I thought, was really
awful, whereas, in Watergate,
like the bumper stickers always

49:28.633 --> 49:30.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
said, nobody died in Watergate.

49:30.266 --> 49:32.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Certainly, our political
system was tarnished.

49:32.633 --> 49:37.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But so many lives in the next
four years, next five years,
if you count Cambodia and

49:39.633 --> 49:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Vietnamese boat people,
almost genocide in Cambodia,
and if the war could have been

49:42.566 --> 49:45.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ended in '68, what a
difference it would have been.

49:45.966 --> 49:48.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Here's a man
who's been written a lot about.

49:48.600 --> 49:52.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
How do you go about
writing a new biography,
and making it fresh?

49:52.333 --> 49:53.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Where do you look?

49:53.333 --> 49:55.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN A. FARRELL: Yes.

49:55.466 --> 49:58.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a great advantage of
being there 40 years later,
because a lot of people have

49:58.600 --> 49:59.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
died.

49:59.700 --> 50:01.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And , privacy
restrictions are lifted.

50:01.833 --> 50:06.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A lot of the national security
restrictions on documents are
worked through, and the stuff

50:06.766 --> 50:08.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
