the one hand, mixed with
this kind of cunning.

50:21.600 --> 50:23.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You humanized him, right?

50:23.800 --> 50:25.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN A. FARRELL: A bit.

50:25.033 --> 50:27.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: You lived
with him a long time.

50:27.166 --> 50:28.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How did you come to see him?

50:28.500 --> 50:29.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN A. FARRELL: Yes.

50:29.533 --> 50:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I developed sympathy for him.

50:31.633 --> 50:36.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was a young teenager
during the 1960s and early
'70s, when he was in office.

50:38.633 --> 50:40.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And he was a villain.

50:40.733 --> 50:45.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But when -- your biography,
inevitably, you open windows
into souls of people, and you

50:47.533 --> 50:51.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
